This command is a classic Unix text processing pipeline that performs **word frequency analysis**. Let me break it down and explain the linguistic implications.

## Command Breakdown

| Stage | Function |
|-------|----------|
| `cat wowfanfic.txt` | Reads your WoW fanfic |
| `perl -ne '@a = split(/\s/); ...` | Splits text into words (on whitespace) |
| `sort` | Alphabetizes all words |
| `uniq -c` | Counts occurrences of each word |
| `sort -n` | Sorts by count (ascending) |
| `tail -n 20` | Shows top 20 most frequent words |

